OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FAmbulance crisis: 'I       
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fthought my mum was going to
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fdie in front of us'        
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, An 86-year-old woman had to wait eight 
OL,6, hours for an ambulance after falling   
OL,7, and breaking her hip at home.          
OL,9,FLillian Briggs, who has Parkinson's,   
OL,10,Fskin cancer and has had two heart      
OL,11,Fattacks, was left lying on her kitchen 
OL,12,Ffloor in agony after blacking out.     
OL,14,FHer son, Robert Ewing, and his sister  
OL,15,Frang for an ambulance a number of times
OL,16,Fonly to be told their mother was in the
OL,17,Fsystem but was not a priority.         
OL,19,FMr Ewing told BBC Scotland: "I thought 
OL,20,Fshe was going to die in front of us."  
